        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 5:10PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Berea, or 22 miles north of Marshall, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Linden, Berea, Lodi, Kildare, Fairview, Avinger, Pruett
and Lassater.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
